Malik Singleton is a data journalist and trainer. He is the founder of the Data Journalism Project, a nonprofit organization that provides training and resources to journalists around the world. He is also the author of the book "Data Journalism: A Practical Guide."

Singleton is a graduate of the University of California, Berkeley, where he studied political science and journalism. He has worked as a reporter for several newspapers, including The New York Times and The Washington Post. He has also worked as a data journalist for The Guardian and ProPublica.

Singleton is a frequent speaker at conferences and workshops on data journalism. He is also a member of the board of directors of the Online News Association.

Singleton is a passionate advocate for the use of data in journalism. He believes that data can be used to tell powerful stories that can inform and engage the public. He is also a strong believer in the power of collaboration and open data.

Singleton is a talented journalist and a gifted teacher. He is a valuable resource for journalists who are interested in learning more about data journalism.
